{
  "texts": [
    "They utilized LSTM with average pooling to represent the essay and neural tensors to model the semantic relationship between two snapshots of hidden representations from the LSTM layer.",
    "As it is shown in Fig. 4, the neural coherence features and the global context information are fed into to a linear layer followed by sigmoid activation function.",
    "The SKIPFLOW mechanism captures global context information and models coherence, however, it overlooks the importance of document modeling.",
    "Li et al. (2018) proposed a coherence-informed essay representation using multi-head self-attention mechanism.",
    "An essay is represented using word-to-word relationships by multi-head self-attention mechanism."
  ]
}